    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 53,
        "summary": "Isaiah speaks about the Messiah\u2014His humiliation and sufferings are described\u2014He makes His soul an offering for sin and makes intercession for the transgressors\u2014Compare Mosiah 14.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Who hath believed our report? and to whom is the arm of the Lord revealed?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 12:38; Rom. 10:16; Mosiah 14:1 (1\u201312).",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For he shall grow up before him as a tender plant, and as a root out of a dry ground: he hath no form nor comeliness; and when we shall see him, there is no beauty that we should desire him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 110:2.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 22:16.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Condescension of.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0it is not for His appearance.",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 153
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He is despised and rejected of men; a man of sorrows, and acquainted with grief: and we hid as it were our faces from him; he was despised, and we esteemed him not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 22:6; Mark 9:12; 1\u00a0Pet. 2:23 (13\u201325). TG\u00a0Malice.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorrow.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 9:11 (10\u201313); John 1:10. TG\u00a0Respect.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 155
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 926
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Surely he hath borne our griefs, and carried our sorrows: yet we did esteem him stricken, smitten of God, and afflicted.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 50:6; Philip. 2:7 (5\u20138).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion; Jesus Christ, Redeemer.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But he was wounded for our transgressions, he was bruised for our iniquities: the chastisement of our peace was upon him; and with his stripes we are healed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Mission of; Jesus Christ, Prophecies about; Salvation, Plan of.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 4:25. TG\u00a0Redemption; Transgress.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 2:24 (24\u201325).",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 142
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Remission of Sins.",
                        "start": 150,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "All we like sheep have gone astray; we have turned every one to his own way; and the Lord hath laid on him the iniquity of us all.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sheep.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:16; 2\u00a0Pet. 2:15 (12\u201315).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 12:5; D&C 1:16. TG\u00a0Selfishness.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 5:21. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Sin.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He was oppressed, and he was afflicted, yet he opened not his mouth: he is brought as a lamb to the slaughter, and as a sheep before her shearers is dumb, so he openeth not his mouth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Oppression.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Affliction.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 14:61; 15:3 (2\u201314).",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 22:8 (8\u201314); Jer. 11:19; Mosiah 14:7 (6\u20138); D&C 135:4. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Lamb of God; Jesus Christ, Trials of.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Persecution.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He was taken from prison and from judgment: and who shall declare his generation? for he was cut off out of the land of the living: for the transgression of my people was he stricken.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 15:10.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Remission of Sins; Transgress.",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 153
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he made his grave with the wicked, and with the rich in his death; because he had done no violence, neither was any deceit in his mouth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 23:32 (32\u201333).",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Death of.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0although.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 2:22.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit; Guile; Honesty.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 126
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Yet it pleased the Lord to bruise him; he hath put him to grief: when thou shalt make his soul an offering for sin, he shall see his seed, he shall prolong his days, and the pleasure of the Lord shall prosper in his hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:15.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 15:10 (5\u201313). TG\u00a0Sons and Daughters of God.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 137
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pleasure.",
                        "start": 174,
                        "end": 182
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 132
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He shall see of the travail of his soul, and shall be satisfied: by his knowledge shall my righteous servant justify many; for he shall bear their iniquities.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Justification.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore will I divide him a portion with the great, and he shall divide the spoil with the strong; because he hath poured out his soul unto death: and he was numbered with the transgressors; and he bare the sin of many, and made intercession for the transgressors.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Crucifixion of; Jesus Christ, Death of; Martyrdom.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 147
                    },
